OL,7,FMears has pleaded not guilty to murder
OL,8,Fbut guilty to the manslaughter of
OL,9,FCatherine.
OL,11,FOn day eight of the trial of Mears,
OL,12,Fthe case hinges on the jury's view of
OL,13,Fthe defendant's mental state at the
OL,14,Ftime he killed Catherine Flynn.
OL,16,FThe court heard from Dr Andrew
OL,17,FShepherd, the psychiatrist speaking on
OL,18,Fbehalf of the defence.
