OL,3,CKiller of grandmother had no
OL,4,C'significant mental disorder', court
OL,5,Chears
OL,7,FHe told the court that Mears came from
OL,8,Fa stable family background with no
OL,9,Fviolence but he had a history of
OL,10,FMental health challenge and had made
OL,11,Fan attempt to take his own life.
OL,13,FThe court was then told that Mears
OL,14,Fbegan to use cannabis at the age 14,
OL,15,Fand cocaine in his early adult life.
OL,17,FThe jury were told that he had
OL,18,Fstruggled with the breakdown of the
OL,19,Frelationship with the mother of his
OL,20,Ftwo children and he began using
OL,21,Fketamine when in a new relationship.
