OL,4,C'significant mental disorder', court
OL,5,Chears
OL,7,FHe also said there is no personality
OL,8,Fdisorder or intellectual impairment,
OL,9,FMears' cognitive function was normal
OL,10,Fand there was no evidence of bipolar
OL,11,Fdisorder.
OL,13,FThe doctor said he had suffered from
OL,14,Fsubstance misuse all his adult life
OL,15,Fbut there is no evidence that this is
OL,16,Fa case of diminished responsibility.
OL,18,FDean Mears admits manslaughter and
OL,19,Fdenied murder and the case continues.
